> We think that crispy pan-fried gnocchi with crème fraîche is not only super tasty
> but incredibly easy to make! The gnocchi has a crispy coating and a pillow-like
> centre, accompanied by 'meaty' chestnut mushrooms, tasty broccoli, cheese and
> flat leaf parsley. We think we've made our own delicacy with this twist on a
> classic Italian dish!

Peel and finely chop the @echalion shallot{1}(peeled and finely chopped) and the
@garlic clove{1}(minced). Clean the @chestnut mushrooms{1}(cleaned with kitchen
paper) and roughly chop. Finely chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(finely chopped).

Heat @oil{1%tbsp} in a #frying pan{} over high heat. Add the mushrooms in small
batches to make sure they go golden brown, then remove from the pan. Fry the
@British smoked bacon lardons{1} in the (now empty) pan, until it has started to
crisp up. Then, add the chopped echalion shallot and garlic and cook for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Return the mushrooms to the pan along with @water{100%ml} and a few grinds of
@black pepper{a few grinds}. Allow to simmer over medium heat for
~{8-10%minutes} until thickened. Meanwhile, bring a #pot{} of water to the boil
with @salt{1/4%tsp}.

In another frying pan, heat @oil{1%tbsp} on medium-high heat. When hot, add the
@gnocchi{350}. Gently fry for ~{8%minutes} until it's crispy around the edges.
Remove from the heat. Meanwhile, cut the @broccoli{1/2}(cut into small florets).
Plunge into the pot of boiling water for ~{3%minutes}, then remove, drain and
keep to the side.

Stir the @crème fraîche{1} into your mushroom sauce. Add your gnocchi and your
broccoli to the sauce and give it all a good stir. Taste for seasoning and add
more salt and pepper as you wish.

Divide your gnocchi between your #bowls{} and top with @parmesan cheese{20}(grated)
and your chopped parsley.